quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  22,39,"Permission is given to those who fight because they have been wronged, and, indeed, Allah has power to give them victory"
  22,40,"Those who have been driven from their homes unjustly only because they said, \"Our Lord is Allah;\" - for were it not for Allah repelling some men by means of others, cloisters and churches and synagogues and mosques, wherein the name of Allah is"
  22,41,"Those who, if We establish them in the land, are steadfast in prayer, and give regular charity, and bid what is right, and forbid what is wrong - with Allah rests the end (final outcome) of affairs"
  22,42,"But if they call you liar, even so did the people of Noah, and the tribes of AÂ´ad and Thamud, they denied (My messengers) before you"
  22,43,"And the people of Abraham, and the people of Lot"
  22,44,"And the dweller of Midian; and Moses was called a liar too: but I indulged the disbelievers a long while, and then I seized them, and how terrible was My rejection"
  22,45,"And how many a city (community) have We destroyed while it was guilty (did wrong), and it tumbled down on its roof, lying ruined to this day, and how many a deserted well and lofty palace"
  22,46,"Have they not travelled through the land? And have they not heart wherewith to feel (understand), and ears wherewith to hear? For, indeed, it is not their eyes that are blind, but it is the hearts which are within their breasts that grow blind"